cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.SY, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) category as it presents a new algorithm for actor-critic reinforcement learning with function approximation. It also involves the use of Gradient Emphasis Learning, which is a novel combination of two existing learning methods, and this could potentially fall under the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) category. The algorithm is designed for robotic applications, which could place it under the Robotics (cs.RO) category. The use of two-timescale learning and off-policy learning could also make it relevant to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) category. Finally, the use of value function critics and the emphasis critic suggests that it could be relevant to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) category.
